==English==
===Etymology===
From Old French [[resjoir]], later [[réjouir]], from [[re-]] + [[esjoir]] (modern French [[éjouir]]), from [[joir]] ‘joy’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/rɪˈʤɔɪs/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|rejoice|rejoices|rejoiced|rejoicing}}

# ''(transitive)'' To make [[happy]], [[exhilirate]].
# ''(intransitive)'' To be very happy, be delighted, [[exult]]; to feel joy.

===Translations===
*Old English: [[gefeon|ġefēon]]

